a4 3
To configure Thunderbird for your language, go to add-ons language 
management (Tools->Add-ons->Languages) and click 'activate' on your
installed language, then restart Thunderbird.
@


1.2
log
@Update to thunderbird-i18n 5.0.
A bunch of languages added (ar,br,en-US,et,fy-NL,gd,gl,is,rm,si,sq,ta-LK),
a bunch of languages removed (af,el,be,gu-IN,mk,zh-CN)..
Install the langpacks as plain xpi instead of unzipping them.
@
text
@d1 3
a3 3
To configure Thunderbird for your language, open the configuration
editor (Preferences->Advanced->Config Editor) and set the
"general.useragent.locale" key to the language you want to use.
@


1.1
log
@Initial revision
@
text
@d1 3
a3 5
To configure Thunderbird for your language, shut down Thunderbird and
add/modifiy these lines to ~/.thunderbird/<something>.default/prefs.js
(e.g. fr-FR ; default is en-US):

user_pref("general.useragent.locale", "fr-FR");
@


